The paper deals with the hardness of a cryptographic problem, Learning with Errors (LWE), which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), and machine learning (cs.LG) to analyze the problem. Additionally, the paper discusses the tradeoff between the dimension and modulus of LWE instances, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DS).
